This paper deals with the deployment of wireless relay networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses learning algorithms for the deployment process, which involves optimization and decision-making, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The formulation of the problem as a Markov decision process (MDP) suggests a connection to control theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
